[[File:darkbrownchullo.jpg|thumb|upright|Alpaca chullo]] '''Chullo''' ({{IPA-es|ˈtʃuʎo}}, from {{lang-ay|ch'ullu}}) is an [[Andes|Andean]] style of [[hat]] with earflaps, made from [[vicuña]], [[alpaca]], [[llama]] or [[sheep]]'s [[wool]].<ref>{{cite book| last = Leslie| first = Catherine Amoroso| title = Needlework Through History: An Encyclopedia| url = https://books.google.com/books?id=pLnWAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA101| year = 2007| publisher = Greenwood Publishing Group| isbn = 978-0-313-33548-8| page = 101 }}</ref> Alpaca has wool-like qualities that help to insulate its wearer from the harsh elements in the [[Andes|Andean Mountain]] region. Chullos often have ear-flaps that can be tied under the chin, to further warm the wearer's head.
Chullos have been used in the [[Andes|Andean Mountain]] region by indigenous peoples for thousands of years. Wearing different types and colors has a significance among certain Andean natives{{citation needed|date=January 2015}}.
In the American TV show [[South Park]], the character [[List of students at South Park Elementary#Craig Tucker|Craig Tucker]] wears a blue chullo.
